This paper is about improving entity typing in natural language processing (NLP) using multiview learning. It combines different views of entity information, such as language and representation, to increase accuracy and coverage of entity type information in knowledge bases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. 

The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as embeddings and multiview learning, which are covered in sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper deals with knowledge bases, which are related to information retrieval (IR) and databases (DB), covered in sub-categories cs.IR and cs.DB, respectively. 

Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.IR and cs.DB.
